f=Shared OS/skills/verification-before-completion/SKILL.md · h2:Overview=Claiming work complete without verification dishonesty, efficiency. **Core principle:** Evidence before claims, always. **Violating letter rule violating spirit rule.** · h2:The Iron Law=`NO COMPLETION CLAIMS WITHOUT FRESH VERIFICATION EVIDENCE` · h2:The Iron Law=you haven't run verification (command, checklist, re-read) claim working session, you cannot make claim. · h2:The Gate Function=`BEFORE claiming any status or expressing satisfaction: \·  \· 1. IDENTIFY: What check proves this claim? \· 2. RUN: Execute the FULL check (fresh, complete) \· 3. READ: Full output — exit codes, failure counts, actual content` · h2:Common Failures=\| Claim \| Requires \| Not Sufficient \| · h2:Common Failures=\|-------\|----------\|----------------\| · h2:Common Failures=\| Tests pass \| Test command output: 0 failures \| Previous run, "should pass" \| · h2:Common Failures=\| Linter clean \| Linter output: 0 errors \| Partial check, extrapolation \| · h2:Common Failures=\| Build succeeds \| Build command: exit 0 \| Linter passing, logs look good \| · h2:Common Failures=\| Bug fixed \| Test of original symptom: passes \| Code changed, assumed fixed \| · h2:Common Failures=\| Regression test works \| Red-green cycle verified \| Test passes once \| · h2:Common Failures=\| Sub-agent completed \| Diff/artifact inspected \| Agent reports "success" \| · h2:Common Failures=\| Requirements met \| Line-by-line checklist against the brief \| Tests passing \| · h2:Common Failures=\| Document/deliverable done \| Re-read against the request, gaps listed \| "Looks finished" \| · h2:Red Flags — STOP=Using "should", "probably", "seems to", Expressing satisfaction before verification ("Great!", "Perfect!", "Done!"), About commit release hand off without verification, Trusting sub-agent's success report, Relying on partial verification, Thinking "just this once", Wanting work over, **ANY wording implying success without having run verification** · h2:Rationalization Prevention=\| Excuse \| Reality \| · h2:Rationalization Prevention=\|--------\|---------\| · h2:Rationalization Prevention=\| "Should work now" \| RUN the verification \| · h2:Rationalization Prevention=\| "I'm confident" \| Confidence ≠ evidence \| · h2:Rationalization Prevention=\| "Just this once" \| No exceptions \| · h2:Rationalization Prevention=\| "Linter passed" \| Linter ≠ compiler \| · h2:Rationalization Prevention=\| "Agent said success" \| Verify independently \| · h2:Rationalization Prevention=\| "Partial check is enough" \| Partial proves nothing \| · h2:Rationalization Prevention=\| "Different words so rule doesn't apply" \| Spirit over letter \| · k:Patterns=**Tests:** [Run tests] [See: 34/34 pass] "All tests pass" "Should pass now" **Regression tests (red-green):** Write Run (pass) Revert fix Run (MUST FAIL) Restore Run (pass) "I've written regression test" without cycle **Build:** [Run build] [exit "Build passes" "Linter passed" **Requirements:** Re-read brief checklist verify report gaps completion "Tests pass, phase complete" **Delegation:** Sub-agent reports success inspect diff/artifact report actual state Trust report · h2:When To Apply=**ALWAYS before:** any success/completion claim paraphrase one, any expression satisfaction, committing/releasing, marking task done, moving next task, delegating onward, handing deliverable another agent operator. · h2:VYON scope & enforcement=**Every agent, department, deliverable type** code, documents, decisions, designs, analyses. decision claimed "formula-verified" requires formula actually run (playbook rule 0.6); document claimed "done" requires re-reading against brief., **Engineering:** quinn enforcement point release gate rejects any "done" arrives without fresh evidence (see quinn/custom/test-strategy charter-enforcement)., skill lives Shared layer only. Agents reference it; they never copy it. · h2:The Bottom Line=Run check. Read output. claim result. Non-negotiable.